From: enfs-dkms
Subject: [PATCH] net/sunrpc/clnt.c: export rpc_task_get_next_xprt for enfs

Stock Ubuntu 7.0 already has the function enfs needs
(rpc_task_get_next_xprt), but it is `static`. enfs's
fs/nfs/enfs/failover_path.c calls it across module boundaries, so
we drop `static` and add EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL.

Same trick that vendored sunrpc.ko itself uses for many helpers; the
patch is two lines.

---
--- a/net/sunrpc/clnt.c
+++ b/net/sunrpc/clnt.c
@@ -1153,11 +1153,12 @@
 	return rpc_task_get_xprt(clnt, xprt);
 }
 
-static struct rpc_xprt *
+struct rpc_xprt *
 rpc_task_get_next_xprt(struct rpc_clnt *clnt)
 {
 	return rpc_task_get_xprt(clnt, xprt_iter_get_next(&clnt->cl_xpi));
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(rpc_task_get_next_xprt);
 
 static
 void rpc_task_set_transport(struct rpc_task *task, struct rpc_clnt *clnt)
